A 17-year-old knocked down and killed as she filled her car with petrol had passed her driving test just days before.

Eilish Herron, 17, from Paisley, Renfrewshire, was struck by a Ford Focus at an Asda petrol station in Linwood yesterday.

She tweeted about passing her driving test on September 1 and was planning to study nursing at University next year.

